    { "risk": "HYPOTHESIS 3 (MEDIUM CONFIDENCE): Cache expiration or degradation. If the service had a cache (in-memory, Redis, etc.) for geocoding or rate lookups that has been gradually losing effectiveness — due to TTL expiration, memory pressure evictions, or growing dataset — more requests hit external APIs directly. Cache hit ratio declining over two weeks matches the gradual pattern.", "severity": "high", "mitigation": "Check cache hit/miss ratios over the past month. If no cache exists, this is itself a finding — geocoding results should absolutely be cached." },
